The paper proposes a model-free learning framework to solve optimization problems with constraints in wireless communications. The use of neural networks for parameterizing the function to be optimized and approximating the unknown objective function or constraints suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of Lagrange multipliers and the connections with reinforcement learning suggest that the paper could also belong to the control systems (cs.SY) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.IT, followed by cs.NE, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
